  "prompt": "What does porcelain mean?",
  "response": "Porcelain is a type of ceramic material known for its strength, translucence, and high resistance to thermal shock. It is made by heating materials, typically including kaolin, in a kiln to temperatures between 1,200 and 1,400 degrees Celsius (2,200 and 2,600 degrees Fahrenheit). Porcelain is often used to make dishes, decorative objects, tile, and other items due to its durability and aesthetic qualities. The term can also refer to items made from this material.",
